---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a href="/courses/ap-csp/" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3">
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Activity 1.8: Numeric Input</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Activity 1.8</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">Numeric Input</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Concepts</h2>
              <p>Type Casting</p>
              <p>parseInt() and parseFloat()</p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>The Problem</h2>
              <p><code>prompt()</code> always returns a string &mdash; even if the user types a number.</p>
              <Code code={Figure1} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
              <p class="fragment">
                <code>+</code> is used for both adding numbers and joining
                text, so when both sides are strings, JavaScript joins them
                instead of adding.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate data-auto-animate-restart>
              <h2>The Fix: Type Casting</h2>
              <p>
                <b class="text-sn-theme">parseInt()</b> and
                <b class="text-sn-theme">parseFloat()</b> convert a string
                into an actual number &mdash; a whole number, or one with
                decimals.
              </p>
              <Code code={Figure2} frame="code" lang="javascript" showLineNumbers={false} />
            </section>

            <section data-auto-animate>
              <h2>A Word of Caution</h2>
              <p>
                If the user types something that isn't a number,
                <code>parseInt()</code>/<code>parseFloat()</code> won't
                crash your program &mdash; they'll silently return
                <b class="text-sn-theme">NaN</b> ("Not a Number"), and any
                math done with it becomes <code>NaN</code> too.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Today's Objectives</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>Converting <code>prompt()</code> input into numbers</li>
                <li>Choosing between <code>parseInt()</code> and <code>parseFloat()</code></li>
                <li>Doing math on converted input</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Key Terms</h2>
              <div class="text-start">
                <dl>
                  <dt>Type Casting</dt>
                  <dd>Converting a value from one type to another, like a string to a number.</dd>
                  <dt>parseInt()</dt>
                  <dd>Converts a string into a whole number.</dd>
                  <dt>parseFloat()</dt>
                  <dd>Converts a string into a number that can have decimals.</dd>
                  <dt>NaN</dt>
                  <dd>"Not a Number" &mdash; the result of trying to convert something that isn't a valid number.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Build -->
        <section id="build">
          <h2>Build</h2>

          <p>
            Create a new JavaScript file named <b class="text-sn-theme">1-8-numeric-input.js</b>.
          </p>

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 1: Age to Months Calculator</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask the user's age, converting it with <code>parseInt()</code>.</li>
            <li>Print their age in months.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task1} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-8-numeric-input.js" mark="3" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 2: Square Area Calculator</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask for the length of a square's side, converting it with <code>parseFloat()</code>.</li>
            <li>Print the square's area.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task2} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-8-numeric-input.js" mark="10" ins="8-14" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 3: Score Calculator</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask for three game scores, converting each with <code>parseFloat()</code>.</li>
            <li>Print their total.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task3} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-8-numeric-input.js" mark="18-20" ins="16-24" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 4: Shopping Cart Subtotal</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask for the prices of two items, converting each with <code>parseFloat()</code>.</li>
            <li>Print their subtotal.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task4} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-8-numeric-input.js" mark="28-29" ins="26-33" />

          <hr class="my-4" />

          <h3>Task 5: Hours to Minutes Converter</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask for a number of hours, converting it with <code>parseFloat()</code>.</li>
            <li>Print the equivalent number of minutes.</li>
          </ul>

          <Code code={Task5} frame="code" lang="javascript" title="1-8-numeric-input.js" mark="37" ins="35-39" />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
        <section id="checkpoint">
          <h2>Checkpoint</h2>

          <p>Verify your program works correctly.</p>

          <Code
            code={SampleOutput}
            frame="terminal"
            lang="txt"
            showLineNumbers={false}
            title="Example Output"
          />
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Reflection -->
        <section id="reflection">
          <h2>Reflection</h2>

          <p>Answer the following questions before submitting your work.</p>

          <ol>
            <li>Why does <code>prompt()</code> always give back a string, even if the user types a number?</li>
            <li>What's the difference between <code>parseInt()</code> and <code>parseFloat()</code>? When would you use one over the other?</li>
            <li>What do you think <code>parseFloat("banana")</code> would return? What might happen if you tried to do math with that result?</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <Divider variant="8" classes="my-5" />

        <!-- Submit -->
        <section id="submit">
          <h2>Submit</h2>

          <p>Submit the required files to the appropriate dropbox.</p>

          <h1
            class="text-center mt-5 text-sn-theme border border-primary slow-flash"
          >
            Activity Complete
          </h1>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
